Wash and dry all produce. Core, seed, and dice the @red bell peppers{2} and @yellow bell pepper{1} into 1-inch pieces. Mince or grate the @garlic{4%cloves}. Thinly slice the @scallions{4}, keeping the greens and whites separate. Chop the @boneless pork chops{24%oz} into bite-sized pieces. Toss in a #large bowl{} with the @cornstarch{2%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

In a #medium pot{}, bring 3 cups water and @veggie stock concentrate{1} to a boil. Once boiling, add the @bulgur wheat{1.5%cup}. Cover and reduce to a low simmer for about ~{15%minutes}, until tender. Fluff with a #fork{}. Season with salt and pepper.

In a #small bowl{}, combine 2 Tablespoons vinegar, @veggie stock concentrate{1}, 2 Tablespoons water, @soy sauce{4%tbsp}, and @sugar{4%tbsp}. Stir to combine.

Heat a thin layer of @olive oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Working in batches, add the pork to the pan. Cook ~{1-2%minutes} per side, until browned. Remove from pan and set aside.

When all the pork is cooked, heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{} in the same pan over medium heat. Add the garlic and scallion whites to the pan. Cook ~{1-2%minutes}, until softened. Add the bell peppers to the pan. Cook, tossing, for ~{4-5%minutes}, until tender. Season with salt and pepper.

Add the pork and sauce to the pan. Toss ~{1-2%minutes}, until the sauce thickens. Serve the sweet-and-sour pork on a bed of bulgur wheat and garnish with the scallion greens. Enjoy!